{'type': 'chat_message', 'role': {'type': 'role', 'value': 'assistant'}, 'contents': [{'type': 'text', 'text': '**Reliable ReAct Loop with Error Recovery & Tool Parallelism (2026 production pattern)**\n\n**Requirements**  \n- LLM: any tool-calling model (e.g. GPT-4o / Claude 3.5+ / open-source equiv.)  \n- Async executor for parallel tool calls (\u22645 concurrent)  \n- Persistent short-term memory (Redis or in-memory) + structured logging  \n- Hard caps: max 12 steps, 30 s total tool time, rate-limit per tool\n\n**Core Modular Snippet (Python 3.12+)**  \n```python\nimport asyncio, logging\nfrom tenacity import retry, stop_after_attempt, wait_exponential\n\nclass ReActAgent:\n    def __init__(self, llm, tools, memory, max_steps=12):\n        self.llm, self.tools, self.memory = llm, tools, memory\n        self.max_steps = max_steps\n        self.log = logging.getLogger("ReAct")\n\n    @retry(stop=stop_after_attempt(3), wait=wait_exponential(multiplier=1, min=1, max=4))\n    async def _call_llm(self, prompt):\n        return await self.llm(prompt)\n\n    async def _run_tools(self, calls):\n        tasks = [asyncio.create_task(self.tools[ c.name ](c.args)) for c in calls]\n        return await asyncio.gather(*tasks, return_exceptions=True)\n\n    async def run(self, goal: str):\n        state = self.memory.get(goal) or []\n        for step in range(self.max_steps):\n            prompt = self._build_prompt(goal, state)\n            action = await self._call_llm(prompt)\n            if action.type == "final": return action.answer\n            try:\n                results = await self._run_tools(action.tool_calls)\n                state.append((action, results))\n            except Exception as e:\n                self.log.error(f"Step {step} failed: {e}")\n                state.append((action, str(e)))\n        raise RuntimeError("Max steps exceeded")\n```\n\n**ASCII Architecture**  \n```\nUser Goal\n   \u2502\n   \u25bc\n[Memory] \u2500\u2500\u25ba [ReAct Loop]\n                \u2502  parallel\n   \u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u253c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\n   \u25bc            \u25bc            \u25bc\nTool A      Tool B      Tool C\n   \u2502            \u2502            \u2502\n   \u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 Retry/Error Handler \u2500\u2518\n                \u2502\n             Final Answer\n```\n\n**Quick Wins & Pitfalls**  \n- Always wrap tools in circuit breakers and input sanitization.  \n- Log every LLM call + tool result hash for audit.  \n- Avoid unbounded loops; enforce step & token budgets.  \n- Test against 2026 benchmarks (AgentBench v2, GAIA, WebArena).\n\nReady for the exact challenge or next pattern (stateful multi-agent orchestration).'}], 'additional_properties': {}}
{'type': 'chat_message', 'role': {'type': 'role', 'value': 'assistant'}, 'contents': [{'type': 'text', 'text': '**Reliable ReAct Loop with Error Recovery & Tool Parallelism (2026 production pattern)**\n\n**Requirements**  \n- LLM: any tool-calling model (e.g. GPT-4o / Claude 3.5+ / open-source equiv.)  \n- Async executor for parallel tool calls (\u22645 concurrent)  \n- Persistent short-term memory (Redis or in-memory) + structured logging  \n- Hard caps: max 12 steps, 30 s total tool time, rate-limit per tool\n\n**Core Modular Snippet (Python 3.12+)**  \n```python\nimport asyncio, logging\nfrom tenacity import retry, stop_after_attempt, wait_exponential\n\nclass ReActAgent:\n    def __init__(self, llm, tools, memory, max_steps=12):\n        self.llm, self.tools, self.memory = llm, tools, memory\n        self.max_steps = max_steps\n        self.log = logging.getLogger("ReAct")\n\n    @retry(stop=stop_after_attempt(3), wait=wait_exponential(multiplier=1, min=1, max=4))\n    async def _call_llm(self, prompt):\n        return await self.llm(prompt)\n\n    async def _run_tools(self, calls):\n        tasks = [asyncio.create_task(self.tools[ c.name ](c.args)) for c in calls]\n        return await asyncio.gather(*tasks, return_exceptions=True)\n\n    async def run(self, goal: str):\n        state = self.memory.get(goal) or []\n        for step in range(self.max_steps):\n            prompt = self._build_prompt(goal, state)\n            action = await self._call_llm(prompt)\n            if action.type == "final": return action.answer\n            try:\n                results = await self._run_tools(action.tool_calls)\n                state.append((action, results))\n            except Exception as e:\n                self.log.error(f"Step {step} failed: {e}")\n                state.append((action, str(e)))\n        raise RuntimeError("Max steps exceeded")\n```\n\n**ASCII Architecture**  \n```\nUser Goal\n   \u2502\n   \u25bc\n[Memory] \u2500\u2500\u25ba [ReAct Loop]\n                \u2502  parallel\n   \u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u253c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\n   \u25bc            \u25bc            \u25bc\nTool A      Tool B      Tool C\n   \u2502            \u2502            \u2502\n   \u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 Retry/Error Handler \u2500\u2518\n                \u2502\n             Final Answer\n```\n\n**Quick Wins & Pitfalls**  \n- Always wrap tools in circuit breakers and input sanitization.  \n- Log every LLM call + tool result hash for audit.  \n- Avoid unbounded loops; enforce step & token budgets.  \n- Test against 2026 benchmarks (AgentBench v2, GAIA, WebArena).\n\nReady for the exact challenge or next pattern (stateful multi-agent orchestration).'}], 'author_name': 'Orchestrator-Agent', 'additional_properties': {}}
