{'type': 'chat_message', 'role': {'type': 'role', 'value': 'assistant'}, 'contents': [{'type': 'text', 'text': '**Risks:** Overly generic advice ignores jurisdiction-specific licensing (e.g., state money-transmitter rules beyond FinCEN) and potential AI liability for financial advice under SEC/FTC rules. Early SOC 2 push drains runway; ReAct agents risk model drift or hallucinated forecasts without rigorous evaluation.\n\n**Tradeoffs:** 4–6 week MVP enables speed but sacrifices security/audit depth; bootstrapped-to-accelerator path trades control for capital; guardrails on AI limit automation benefits.\n\n**Missing assumptions:** Exact product (forecasting vs. lending), founder regulatory experience, target states/countries, customer data sensitivity, and AI model provider (open vs. closed).\n\n**Mitigations:** Engage fintech counsel for jurisdiction mapping before incorporation; pilot AI in read-only mode with mandatory human sign-off; delay SOC 2 to post-revenue; run weekly compliance checklists and third-party red-team AI outputs.'}], 'additional_properties': {}}
