{'type': 'chat_message', 'role': {'type': 'role', 'value': 'assistant'}, 'contents': [{'type': 'text', 'text': 'Practical Plan for 2026 Fintech Startup Launch\n\nPriorities: Regulatory compliance first, rapid market validation, lean AI-integrated MVP, and risk-managed scaling to secure early funding.\n\nSteps:\n1. **Validate in 2 weeks**: Define one core pain point (e.g., SME invoice financing). Conduct 20 customer interviews; test with no-code prototype (Retool + Stripe + Supabase).\n2. **Secure compliance**: Incorporate in Delaware, budget $15-50k for legal setup, including money transmitter licenses and FinCEN KYC. Engage specialist counsel immediately.\n3. **Build MVP (4-6 weeks)**: Use Python/FastAPI, React, PostgreSQL + Redis. Integrate guarded ReAct AI agents for fraud checks, document parsing, and advice with human-in-loop oversight and audit logs.\n4. **Fund & de-risk**: Target accelerator pre-seed (YC, a16z) for 12-18 months runway. Implement SOC 2 prep, model monitoring, and disclaimers in month 3.\n5. **Iterate**: Launch prototype, gather metrics, refine AI patterns and compliance before full product build.\n\nThis sequence minimizes legal exposure while delivering production-ready tech.'}], 'additional_properties': {}}
