{'type': 'chat_message', 'role': {'type': 'role', 'value': 'user'}, 'contents': [{'type': 'text', 'text': '**Task brief:** User intends to launch a fintech startup. Deliver concise, actionable recommendations covering validation, compliance, MVP build, tech (incl. AI agent patterns), funding, and key risks. Prioritize production-ready steps for 2026.\n\n**Final recommendations**  \n1. **Validate fast**: Build a no-code MVP (Stripe + Supabase + Retool) targeting one pain point (e.g., SME cash-flow forecasting or instant invoice financing). Talk to 20 prospects in 2 weeks.  \n2. **Compliance first**: Incorporate in Delaware, obtain necessary licenses (money transmitter, broker-dealer, or RIA). Use tools like Shoreline or FinCEN-compliant KYC from day one. Budget $15-50k legal.  \n3. **Tech stack**: Python/FastAPI backend, React frontend, PostgreSQL + Redis. Add reliable ReAct-style AI agents for document parsing, fraud detection, and personalized advice (with strict guardrails and human-in-loop).  \n4. **MVP scope**: 4–6 weeks to working prototype. Focus on core flow + audit logging; skip nice-to-haves.  \n5. **Funding & runway**: Bootstrapped \u2192 pre-seed via fintech accelerators (Y Combinator, a16z Crypto, or Visa/ Mastercard programs). Target 12–18 months runway.  \n6. **Risk mitigations**: Data privacy (SOC 2 from month 3), model drift monitoring for AI components, and clear disclaimers on automated decisions.  \n\nReady to refine once you share the specific fintech idea or pain point.'}], 'additional_properties': {}}
