{'type': 'chat_message', 'role': {'type': 'role', 'value': 'assistant'}, 'contents': [{'type': 'text', 'text': '**Facts:** 16-week launch plan for a new-city online grocery service targeting first delivery by week 16. Includes 3 phases: validation (weeks 1-4), pre-launch beta (5-8), and scale (9-16). Targets 1,000 orders/day, 20–25 stores, 100 drivers. Budget: ~$400k first 6 months. KPIs: >92% on-time, <15% churn. AI forecasting introduced after week 12.\n\n**Context:** Hyper-local urban rollout using white-label tech, gig drivers, one micro-hub, and geo-fenced marketing to differentiate via 2-hour delivery and fresh guarantee.\n\n**Assumptions:** 500 beta users convert quickly; real-time inventory APIs available from partners; dense neighborhoods generate sufficient demand; weekly A/B tests and early data team will optimize operations without major delays.\n\n**Useful examples:** Phased MVP validation with 50 interviews + Google Trends; 100% fresh + strict time windows as core value props; daily KPI dashboard starting at 50-order scale before full ramp.'}], 'additional_properties': {}}
