{'type': 'chat_message', 'role': {'type': 'role', 'value': 'user'}, 'contents': [{'type': 'text', 'text': '**College Student Support Chatbot: Research, Strategy & Risks**\n\n**Research Summary (2026)**  \nStudent chatbots now handle 65-75% of routine queries (scheduling, financial aid, mental health resources, course registration). Leading institutions use hybrid RAG + agent systems with strict guardrails. Key success factors: domain-specific knowledge bases, seamless human escalation, and bias monitoring. Average resolution rate improves to 80%+ when multi-agent orchestration separates intent detection from knowledge retrieval and compliance checks.\n\n**Implementation Strategy**\n\n**Phase 1 (Weeks 1-4)**: Define scope (top 20 query categories) and build knowledge base from existing FAQs, policy docs, and registrar data. Choose stack: LangChain/LlamaIndex + vector store (Pinecone or self-hosted) + LLM with tool-calling.\n\n**Phase 2 (Weeks 5-8)**: Deploy modular multi-agent architecture:  \n- Router Agent (classifies query)  \n- Knowledge Agent (RAG retrieval)  \n- Action Agent (integrates with calendar, SIS, or ticketing systems)  \n- Compliance Agent (flags sensitive topics like mental health for immediate human handoff)  \n\nUse reliable ReAct loops with parallel tool calls, max 6 turns, and full audit logging.\n\n**Phase 3 (Weeks 9-12)**: Pilot with 500 students, A/B test against current email/phone support. Integrate via web widget, mobile app, and SMS.\n\n**Phase 4 (Ongoing)**: Continuous fine-tuning on anonymized transcripts + quarterly bias audits.\n\n**Risks & Mitigations**  \n- Hallucinated academic advice \u2192 Mandatory RAG + disclaimer on every answer; escalate any policy-related query.  \n- Data privacy (FERPA) \u2192 On-prem or private-cloud deployment; PII redaction layer; SOC 2 + annual audits.  \n- Bias or unequal access \u2192 Diverse training data, regular fairness testing, and accessibility compliance (WCAG 2.2).  \n- Over-reliance \u2192 Clear “talk to human” button; SLA for escalation under 2 minutes.  \n- Security \u2192 Rate limiting, input sanitization, and immutable conversation logs.\n\n**Clear Recommendations**  \nStart with a narrow, high-volume scope (advising + financial aid). Budget $80-120k for MVP. Prioritize human-in-the-loop for any mental health or academic standing queries. Measure success via CSAT, resolution rate, and escalation volume. Iterate monthly based'}], 'additional_properties': {}}
