{'type': 'chat_message', 'role': {'type': 'role', 'value': 'user'}, 'contents': [{'type': 'text', 'text': '**90-Day Safe Generative AI Adoption Plan for Small Companies**\n\n**Goal**  \nEnable productive use of generative AI (writing, coding, research, customer support) while blocking data leaks, hallucinations, and compliance risks.\n\n**Days 1–30: Foundation & Guardrails**  \n- Appoint one AI lead and legal/HR reviewer.  \n- Create AI Use Policy: no customer PII, trade secrets, or financial data in prompts.  \n- Approve 2–3 tools only (e.g., ChatGPT Team, Claude Pro, GitHub Copilot).  \n- Run mandatory 1-hour training for all staff on safe prompting and output verification.  \n- Pilot: one department uses AI for internal documents only.\n\n**Days 31–60: Controlled Pilots**  \n- Launch 3 narrow use cases: email drafting, code review assistance, meeting summaries.  \n- Add mandatory human review + source citation for any external output.  \n- Implement logging and prompt-redaction tools.  \n- Set usage KPIs: 20% of eligible tasks attempted with AI.\n\n**Days 61–90: Scale & Monitor**  \n- Expand to customer-facing content (with disclaimer) and sales materials.  \n- Quarterly bias/hallucination spot-checks.  \n- Review first incidents and update policy.  \n- Decide on paid enterprise plan or self-hosted alternative.\n\n**Safety Controls (non-negotiable)**  \n- All prompts go through a redaction layer.  \n- Max 3 approved LLMs; no shadow tools.  \n- Weekly usage report to leadership.  \n- Immediate human escalation for any regulatory or financial output.\n\n**Recommendations**  \nStart with policy and training before any tool access. Measure success by time saved and incident count (target: zero data leaks). Re-evaluate budget for enterprise plans at Day 60.'}], 'additional_properties': {}}
